annotationA: Probable methylmalonate-semialdehyde dehydrogenase [acylating], mitochondrial; Plays a role in valine and pyrimidine metabolism. Binds fatty acyl-CoA (By similarity); Belongs to the aldehyde dehydrogenase family
annotationB: Dihydrolipoamide acetyltransferase component of pyruvate dehydrogenase complex; Dihydrolipoamide branched chain acyltransferase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: phagocytosis; tricarboxylic acid cycle
